1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. d4 exd4 4. Nxd4 Bc5 5. Nf5 $6 {This is an optimistic
move. Attacking the pawn on g7, but...} d5 $1 {Black ignores the threat and
allows to take the pawn with check in the style of old masters!} 6. Nxg7+ ({
After} 6. Qxd5 $2 Qxd5 7. exd5 Nb4 {[%csl Rc2,Rf5] Black wins material.}) 6...
Kf8 7. Nh5 ({Worse is} 7. Nf5 $2 Bxf5 8. exf5 Qh4 {[%csl Rf2]} 9. Qf3 Re8+ 10.
Kd1 Nf6 {[%csl Rf2][%cal Gf6e4,Gc6d4] and White will not survive the attack.})
7... Qh4 8. Ng3 Nf6 {Development above all! Black has already four actively
developed pieces, while White has only one knight on g3. It's clear that Black
has the initiative.} 9. Be2 {White can't be greedy and has to complete the
development to avoid a quick catastrophy.} (9. exd5 $2 {leads to a disaster.}
Ng4 $1 10. dxc6 Bxf2+ 11. Kd2 Qh6+ 12. Kc3 Qxc6+ 13. Bc4 Qf6+ 14. Kb3 Qb6+ 15.
Kc3 c5 $1 {There is no immediate mate, but black's attack is decisive.}) 9...
Rg8 {Black has other good options, such as 9...dxe4, 9...Bg4 or 9...Ng4, but I
like the idea of using the "g" file.} 10. Nc3 (10. exd5 $2 {is bad again in
view of} Ng4 11. Bxg4 Bxg4 12. Qd3 Re8+ 13. Be3 (13. Kf1 {loses to} {[%tqu
"En","How can Black win the queen?","","","g4e2","",10]} Be2+ $1 $19 {[%cal
Gh4f2,Gc5f2]}) 13... Bxe3 14. fxe3 Nb4 15. Qd2 Rxe3+ $1 {[%csl Rc2] With a
crushing attack.}) 10... dxe4 {Now the material is equal. As already mentioned,
Black has lost the right to castle. The pawn structure is not ideal either.
However, in current position Black's activity and advantage in development is
the dominant factor, therefore his chances are preferable here.} 11. O-O Be6
12. Be3 Bd6 13. Qd2 a6 14. Na4 Rg6 15. Nc5 Ne5 $1 {Who cares about the
structure!? Go for the initiative!} 16. Nxe6+ fxe6 17. Rad1 Kg8 $1 {Preparing
the way for the queenside rook.} 18. Qd4 Rf8 {Black's last reserve joins the
attack.} 19. Kh1 Rf7 20. a3 Neg4 21. h3 Nh2 $1 {Very nice idea! White decided
to put an end to his suffering and resigned here in the game 0-1 (21) Herzog,K
(2158) -Breuer,R (2275) GER email 2008. He has to give an exchange for nothing,
to avoid the worst.} (21... Nh2 $1 22. Rg1 (22. Kxh2 Rxg3 $1 $19) 22... Rxg3 $1
23. fxg3 Qxg3 24. Bf2 {[%tqu "En","How should Black continue his attack?","",
"","h2f1","Really spectacular!",10]} Nf1 $3 {Really spectacular!} 25. Bxg3
Nxg3+ 26. Kh2 Nxe2+ $19) *

